About the Business

Eat Well. No Compromises. Real food is born of goodness.It's good to source fresh ingredients locally, sustainably, and ethically. It's good to create chef-crafted meals that are as nutritious and delicious as they are wholesome. Whether you're vegetarian, vegan, pescatarian, or a straight-up carnivore, we have a plate that you're going to feel good about eating. Oh yeah, it's also going to be delicious. And it's not going to break the bank.We're about real food and nixing compromises you have to make to eat that way. If you're into the power of real food and being good to the world that made it,then we're a place you're going to like.Welcome to our table.

    I met some friends here for lunch recently and we really enjoyed it. We have been here several times over the last couple of years. With the pandemic, they have completely changed their way of ordering and the menu itself. You now go to the cashier and order what you want then they give you a number and they bring the food to you at your table. The have added an extra outdoor patio on the front of the restaurant, plus the side patio that was there previously. And there are still some tables inside as well. They also have a water station with pre-filled cups of water with lids for you to take.

    I had the CHICKPEA + SWEET POTATO bowl: organic lentils, organic chickpeas, agave roasted sweet potatoes, julienne red cabbage, green peas, goji berries, harissa sauce and kale pesto. This was so good. Loved everything in it and the flavors were so yummy. I am not vegan but sometimes enjoy stuff without meat. So good. Also, came with a side of nicely grilled sourdough bread.

    One friend had a chicken sandwich and another had the chicken plate. Both really enjoyed their meals too. And one had the hummingbird cake. She really liked this. Said it was tasty and light, not too heavy.

    Overall a nice lunch. We will be back.

    CHICKPEA + SWEET POTATO BOWL

    My friends and I had lunch here recently and really enjoyed it. You order at the counter at different stations depending on whether you want a salad, sandwich or hot item.

    I had the Chicken Cobb salad: lettuce blend, tomatoes, turkey bacon, avocado, egg (I held this), blue cheese, and buttermilk dill dressing. It was very tasty. Loved the dressing with its mild dill flavor. And you can't go wrong with avocado and blue cheese. I also got a chocolate macaroon. The coconut flavor was so good and lots of melted chocolate on top. It was always too hard to eat since the chocolate was melting.

    One friend had the grilled chicken sandwich. She really liked it, especially the roasted tomatoes on it. I can't remember what the other friend had but she liked her dish too.

    We have been here several times and it has always been tasty. Good and friendly service.

    1/8/2019Previous review

    My friends and I met for lunch here recently and really enjoyed it. They have really nice comfort food. The restaurant is sort of like a cafeteria. You order food at the station you want. Then you pay at the end.

    I had the braised beef & mushrooms bowl with natural beef slow cooked with red wine sauce, mushrooms, onions and organic carrots. It came with a side of mashed potatoes. The beef was really tasty, cooked nicely so it was really tender. Loved the mushrooms and carrots in it. The mashed potatoes were creamy and really delicious. The only sour note was the side of Brussel sprouts I got. They seemed to be boiled, not roasted. They were too soft and mushy. No real flavor.

    My friend was disappointed the no longer had her favorite meal but she got something else that she liked. I think it was a salmon dish. My other friend had meatloaf and really liked it.

    Overall a nice place for a casual comfort food lunch.

    9/14/2016Previous review

    My friends and I were checking out this new shopping center and decided to do lunch here. They have tons of healthy stuff - salads, meats, sandwiches, stews. I had the wonderful moroccan chicken braise - free range chicken simmered with squash, onions, preserved lemon, olives, turmeric, paprika, cumin, ginger, cinnamon, parlsey, cilantro (gluten-free & dairy-free). It was super tasty, lots of good veggies, nice spice. I also had a side of the roasted brussels sprouts with turkey bacon. They were nicely roasted, a bit charred. My friends had a variety of soup, flatbreads and salads. Definitely a fast, healthy option for lunch or dinner. The desserts looked awesome too. One friend bought a chocolate peanut butter cupcake for later. She said it was very rich and delicious. My friends and I hang out in Dublin often so this definitely will be a place we hit for lunch again.

    The food here is amazing! They have locations throughout CA, and I was excited to hear that they will be opening up a location in Sunnyvale this fall. Yipee!!

    I wish there were more places like this- affordable but high quality delicious food, casual and quick food yet in a beautiful indoor and outdoor space.

    From their $10 menu we ordered two dishes:
    Moroccan Chicken meal. The chicken was tendered and came in a tasty, slightly spicy sauce base. It was a hearty dish that reminded me of cozy chicken dinners we make out of our crock pot sometimes.
    Beet and Avocado bowl- colorful, quinoa based dish. It was very tasty but also light and healthy.
    Seriously such an amazing deal that these dishes were $10!

    From their plates menu I ordered the
    Meatless Loaf- SO AMAZING! I loved the texture which was both soft and juicy but also had some grit to it. It's quinoa, black bean based. You get two pick two sides and there are so many amazing sides to choose from!

    I ordered on their website for pick-up. Not the easiest website to navigate and could be streamlined a little, but it was fine.
    This location made pick-up a cinch. Packages are really nicely sealed, lined up on the shelves. They even have water in lidded plastic cups for you to grab as well.

    Almost forgot to mention- I got their passion fruit coconut lime drink that was also AMAZING. I just imagined some sweetened spritzer, but it had this creaminess to the drink, and tasted very naturally sweetened. It was like nothing I'd had recently!

I'd recommend that, as they seem to get busy, and my in-person takeout order took a good chunk of time to prepare, maybe 15 minutes. They have indoor seating but there were very few people Sitting inside, and more on a covered patio on the parking lot space outside on Astro turf. The staff was friendly. I tried the Moroccan braised chicken bowl with brown rice and no bread, and Blueberry lemonade. Both were good, plenty of chicken in the dish, and also a bunch of squash. The blueberry lemonade tasted like real fruit, and it wasn't watery.

  • Michelle P.

    Elite '2021

    San Jose, CA
    24
    96
    359
    12/5/2020
    2 photos

    We were looking for a place to eat after shopping at the outlets and I was so ecstatic to see Urban Plates in NorCal!

    The inside is incredibly spacious and beautifully lit; however, due to covid, they have organized a super socially distanced outside dining area. All the tables were spaced out more than 6 feet from each other, which we greatly appreciated. It was a bit chilly and I wish there were some heaters outside because our food got cold quickly. It took a bit long for our orders to come out.. I think about 30 mins and this was interesting because there wasn't any one else sitting outside waiting for their food. We had ordered a drink & when our food came out, we let the waiter know we never got our drink. Instead of apologizing for the mix up, he told us we should have gotten our drink. Well, if we had gotten I drink, it would have been on the table! Either way, he did get our drink eventually. I believe we got the passion fruit coconut lime. It was nothing too special.

    Chimichurri steak w green beans & mashed potatoes - Though it seems like it's only a few pieces of steak, it is actually a really filling meal. I love the chimichurri flavor on the steak. I feel that it goes well with the steak and without it, it could be rather bland. The green beans & mushrooms weren't spicy as described nonetheless were tasty. The mashed potatoes and gravy was so delicious to dip the steak pieces in. I could probably pass on the rustic bread.

    Meatless loaf w potatoes & Mac n cheese - This was surprisingly really tasty and reminds me of a vegetarian spaghetti meatball! It was filling as well. I didn't really like the potatoes. They were rather dry and starchy and I could only eat it when dipped in the mashed potatoes from the chimichurri dish. The mac n cheese was super cheesy and I definitely enjoy my cheese; however, I felt like most of my food was cold when it came out. So that kinda ruined the experience.

    Hummingbird cake slice - 10/10 if you love banana bread and walnuts, this is for you. The frosting is so good and it's not overwhelmingly sweet either. The cake itself is really soft and moist.

    Overall, I do feel like the food is good but I think service wise could have been a lot more attentive and friendlier.

    chimichurri steak w green beans & mashed potatoes

    meatless loaf w potatoes & Mac n cheese
